      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausages have browned, add the <strong>diced shallot </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 30 secs further</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has reduced – this is your <strong>spicy meat-free sausage sauce</strong></p>",
